30
00:02:03.945 --> 00:02:05.255
Now. every year.

31
00:02:05.368 --> 00:02:08.298
the world's Golf GTI enthusiasts congregate

32
00:02:08.637 --> 00:02:11.243
in a field in Austria and they talk about fuel injection

33
00:02:11.326 --> 00:02:13.637
and wear jumpers with "GTI" on them and. frankly.

34
00:02:13.736 --> 00:02:15.398
I'd rather blowtorch my nipples off.

35
00:02:15.449 --> 00:02:16.111
but...

36
00:02:16.619 --> 00:02:18.986
Volkswagen. every year. sends them a little present -

37
00:02:19.028 --> 00:02:20.606
a concept car of some kind.

38
00:02:20.641 --> 00:02:22.088
to say. "Thank you for your loyalty."

39
00:02:22.394 --> 00:02:23.281
This year. though.

40
00:02:23.569 --> 00:02:24.413
disaster.

41
00:02:24.565 --> 00:02:26.041
Volkswagen forgot.

42
00:02:26.109 --> 00:02:27.518
Eight weeks to go.

43
00:02:27.563 --> 00:02:29.355
They had to build something. anything.

44
00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:30.426
to keep the fans happy.

45
00:02:33.252 --> 00:02:36.517
Luckily. Volkswagen owns lots of other car companies -

46
00:02:36.935 --> 00:02:37.476
Bentley.

47
00:02:37.566 --> 00:02:38.456
Bugatti.

48
00:02:38.558 --> 00:02:39.535
Lamborghini.

49
00:02:39.614 --> 00:02:40.595
Skoda.

50
00:02:40.663 --> 00:02:41.170
Audi

51
00:02:41.215 --> 00:02:42.173
and Seat

52
00:02:42.395 --> 00:02:43.522
so they had a big bin

53
00:02:43.567 --> 00:02:45.416
to rummage around in for parts.

54
00:02:47.073 --> 00:02:47.918
What they did. then.

55
00:02:47.964 --> 00:02:49.069
with the clock ticking.

56
00:02:49.114 --> 00:02:51.075
was take the rear axle and brakes

57
00:02:51.132 --> 00:02:52.800
from a Lamborghini Gallardo.

58
00:02:53.024 --> 00:02:56.008
the twin turbo-charged W12 engine

59
00:02:56.078 --> 00:02:57.596
from a Bentley Continental.

60
00:02:57.642 --> 00:03:00.008
and the rear sub-frame and floor

61
00:03:00.065 --> 00:03:01.166
from an Audi R8.

62
00:03:01.223 --> 00:03:04.029
And then. they put all these bits and pieces

63
00:03:04.108 --> 00:03:06.103
in the body of a Golf.

64
00:03:08.306 --> 00:03:09.726
And here it is.

65
00:03:11.755 --> 00:03:14.310
It's called the GTI W12.

66
00:03:14.355 --> 00:03:16.531
and unlike most concept cars.

67
00:03:16.813 --> 00:03:18.444
it actually works.

68
00:03:21.465 --> 00:03:22.265
Sort of.

69
00:03:24.485 --> 00:03:25.891
As you'd expect with a car

70
00:03:26.319 --> 00:03:27.581
made so quickly.

71
00:03:27.717 --> 00:03:29.430
there are one or two issues.

72
00:03:29.569 --> 00:03:30.997
The paddles here on the steering wheel

73
00:03:31.053 --> 00:03:32.699
for the gearbox don't work.

74
00:03:32.951 --> 00:03:34.569
Er. these switches here.

75
00:03:34.935 --> 00:03:35.854
they don't work.

76
00:03:35.950 --> 00:03:37.087
Sat-nav does work.

77
00:03:37.147 --> 00:03:38.614
but thinks it's in Germany.

78
00:03:38.996 --> 00:03:41.807
And these heating and ventilation knobs

79
00:03:42.062 --> 00:03:43.603
they're not connected to anything.

80
00:03:43.689 --> 00:03:44.922
So I'm very hot.

81
00:03:46.122 --> 00:03:47.490
The six-litre.

82
00:03:47.548 --> 00:03:49.106
640hp.

83
00:03:49.226 --> 00:03:50.495
12-cylinder engine. though...

84
00:03:51.215 --> 00:03:52.696
..that works...

85
00:03:52.816 --> 00:03:53.796
just fine.

86
00:03:57.140 --> 00:03:58.123
As a result.

87
00:03:58.257 --> 00:04:00.164
this car will get from 0 - 60

88
00:04:00.222 --> 00:04:02.129
in 3.5 seconds!

89
00:04:04.094 --> 00:04:05.803
And it will keep on accelerating

90
00:04:05.937 --> 00:04:07.998
all the way to 202.

91
00:04:10.753 --> 00:04:13.237
To contain all the power and the fury.

92
00:04:13.315 --> 00:04:15.967
the W12 is 6 inches wider

93
00:04:16.102 --> 00:04:17.123
and 3 inches lower

94
00:04:17.239 --> 00:04:18.606
than a normal Golf.

95
00:04:21.952 --> 00:04:24.167
The roof is made from carbon fibre.

96
00:04:24.783 --> 00:04:27.865
The tyres sit like smears of paint on the wheels.

97
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:28.963
and the engine

98
00:04:29.059 --> 00:04:31.814
is where you'd expect to find the back seats.

99
00:04:32.625 --> 00:04:33.531
To cool it.

100
00:04:33.627 --> 00:04:35.649
there are massive intake vents in the sills.

101
00:04:36.073 --> 00:04:38.192
That's why the bottom of the car is swollen

102
00:04:38.288 --> 00:04:39.945
like your granny's ankles.

103
00:04:40.099 --> 00:04:42.790
And they made all these changes in just eight weeks.

104
00:04:43.907 --> 00:04:45.679
However did they lose?

105
00:04:47.118 --> 00:04:48.890
The funny thing is. you sit here.

106
00:04:48.967 --> 00:04:50.238
looking at a Golf dashboard

107
00:04:50.315 --> 00:04:51.124
and a Golf bonnet.

108
00:04:51.201 --> 00:04:52.126
through a Golf windscreen.

109
00:04:52.242 --> 00:04:52.954
and you think.

110
00:04:53.301 --> 00:04:54.187
"It's a Golf."

111
00:04:55.285 --> 00:04:56.826
But it so isn't!

112
00:05:00.884 --> 00:05:02.888
It's not a particularly savage car.

113
00:05:03.010 --> 00:05:04.917
It doesn't explode when you

114
00:05:05.033 --> 00:05:06.954
stamp on the accelerator.

115
00:05:07.994 --> 00:05:09.323
It's just this

116
00:05:09.439 --> 00:05:12.001
surge of power that takes you up to

117
00:05:12.829 --> 00:05:14.312
5.500rpm.

118
00:05:14.505 --> 00:05:15.559
And then.

119
00:05:15.655 --> 00:05:18.217
the surge becomes a flood.

120
00:05:19.295 --> 00:05:20.798
I can't get away from it!

121
00:05:31.458 --> 00:05:34.155
It is an insane car. this.

122
00:05:34.534 --> 00:05:38.367
Opening up a Golf to find it has 640hp is like

123
00:05:38.483 --> 00:05:40.428
opening up Gordon Brown's trousers

124
00:05:40.544 --> 00:05:42.855
and finding he's wearing stockings and suspenders.

125
00:05:43.678 --> 00:05:44.680
Mad.

126
00:05:45.219 --> 00:05:47.280
Unfortunately. there is

127
00:05:47.357 --> 00:05:49.168
a small problem...

128
00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:52.475
This car

129
00:05:52.591 --> 00:05:54.941
will not go round corners.

130
00:06:04.047 --> 00:06:05.896
The wheelbase is short.

131
00:06:05.973 --> 00:06:07.553
and it's rear-wheel drive

132
00:06:07.649 --> 00:06:08.978
so you have to be

133
00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:10.750
extremely gentle.

134
00:06:10.885 --> 00:06:11.765
You have to

135
00:06:11.881 --> 00:06:13.768
treat all the controls like they're

136
00:06:14.192 --> 00:06:15.271
made of glass.

137
00:06:17.833 --> 00:06:20.221
Even if you're really gentle.

138
00:06:20.639 --> 00:06:22.604
you'll still... Yes. yes.

139
00:06:26.283 --> 00:06:28.941
You'll still end up coming out of the corner backwards. like that.

140
00:06:29.013 --> 00:06:30.322
I meant that...

141
00:06:35.003 --> 00:06:37.083
Tame the under-steer. there's a lot of it... I've got it!

142
00:06:37.353 --> 00:06:38.528
No. I haven't!

143
00:06:41.413 --> 00:06:42.261
An hour later

144
00:06:42.338 --> 00:06:44.399
I reckoned I was getting somewhere.

145
00:06:44.457 --> 00:06:45.046
Come.

146
00:06:45.166 --> 00:06:45.990
come.

147
00:06:46.110 --> 00:06:47.011
come.

148
00:06:47.131 --> 00:06:48.323
COME!

149
00:06:48.785 --> 00:06:49.690
Yes...

150
00:07:00.247 --> 00:07:02.173
That doesn't work. either.

151
00:07:02.597 --> 00:07:06.039
I think the kindest thing I can say about

152
00:07:06.367 --> 00:07:09.082
the brakes and suspension is

153
00:07:09.333 --> 00:07:11.220
they're...not finished yet.

154
00:07:14.352 --> 00:07:16.416
You're such a spanner!

155
00:07:19.959 --> 00:07:22.695
It just goes. "Eurgh!"
and there's smoke everywhere.

156
00:07:22.733 --> 00:07:23.292
You were.

157
00:07:23.349 --> 00:07:23.792
I wasn't.

158
00:07:23.812 --> 00:07:24.268
You were.

159
00:07:24.299 --> 00:07:24.659
I wasn't.

160
00:07:24.858 --> 00:07:26.480
Let me get one thing clear.

161
00:07:26.732 --> 00:07:28.480
This isn't going to go on sale. is it?

162
00:07:28.563 --> 00:07:31.111
No. Volkswagen sent it to us cos they said.

163
00:07:31.174 --> 00:07:33.533
"If people like it. we'll put it into production."

164
00:07:33.786 --> 00:07:35.492
They're not going to get any encouragement from me.

165
00:07:35.660 --> 00:07:37.661
To be honest. that is ghastly.

166
00:07:37.766 --> 00:07:39.346
My biggest problem with it

167
00:07:40.146 --> 00:07:41.620
I can't see the point to say.

168
00:07:41.599 --> 00:07:42.524
"I've got a supercar

169
00:07:42.629 --> 00:07:44.356
and the great thing is. it looks like a Golf."

170
00:07:44.462 --> 00:07:47.052
That's like saying. "I'm married to a supermodel and the great thing is.

171
00:07:47.157 --> 00:07:48.653
she looks like a traffic warden!"

172
00:07:48.779 --> 00:07:50.443
It doesn't make any sense.

173
00:07:50.506 --> 00:07:52.254
Even so. we must now see

174
00:07:52.380 --> 00:07:54.592
how quickly it can crash on our track.

175
00:07:55.055 --> 00:07:55.876
And for that.

176
00:07:55.982 --> 00:07:57.753
we need our tame racing driver.

177
00:07:57.881 --> 00:08:00.153
Yeah. some say that his scrotum

178
00:08:00.245 --> 00:08:02.022
has its own small gravity field.

179
00:08:03.781 --> 00:08:05.632
And that because our producer

180
00:08:05.724 --> 00:08:07.648
rigged a phone-vote.

181
00:08:07.721 --> 00:08:09.609
he now has a new name.

182
00:08:10.221 --> 00:08:11.504
All we know is

183
00:08:11.578 --> 00:08:12.879
he's called "Cuddles".

184
00:08:14.858 --> 00:08:15.408
And he's off.

185
00:08:15.481 --> 00:08:16.965
We know this car is frisky

186
00:08:17.002 --> 00:08:18.413
but if anyone can tame it.

187
00:08:18.468 --> 00:08:19.952
this is the man.

188
00:08:20.942 --> 00:08:21.986
First corner.

189
00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:23.434
twitchy on the braking.

190
00:08:23.489 --> 00:08:24.918
Tyres howling in pain.

191
00:08:24.992 --> 00:08:27.062
Back on the power. Nicely done.

192
00:08:28.361 --> 00:08:30.230
No CD today. because

193
00:08:30.322 --> 00:08:31.916
predictably. the stereo doesn't work.

194
00:08:32.521 --> 00:08:33.913
OK. through Chicago.

195
00:08:34.390 --> 00:08:35.984
Nursing it round there carefully.

196
00:08:36.094 --> 00:08:38.641
Another huge surge of power. coming up to Hammerhead.

197
00:08:39.209 --> 00:08:40.547
Wiggling its hips under the brakes.

198
00:08:40.639 --> 00:08:41.940
He's chucked it in.

199
00:08:42.325 --> 00:08:44.249
It's in... It's biting back!

200
00:08:44.902 --> 00:08:47.651
Ooh. he's having to fight it every inch of the way.

201
00:08:49.136 --> 00:08:49.997
Listen to that.

202
00:08:50.299 --> 00:08:53.182
In the Bentley. that engine is as quiet as a startled deer.

203
00:08:53.241 --> 00:08:55.409
Here. it's like being chased by an imploding star!

204
00:08:56.393 --> 00:08:57.659
And about as scary.

205
00:08:59.018 --> 00:08:59.733
Winding it up.

206
00:08:59.792 --> 00:09:01.500
here he comes now. through the tyres.

207
00:09:02.321 --> 00:09:03.680
Oh. yeah. Looking good.

208
00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:04.418
Ish.

209
00:09:05.192 --> 00:09:07.196
Just two accidents waiting to happen.

210
00:09:07.243 --> 00:09:09.340
Turns in. look at the over-steer!

211
00:09:09.399 --> 00:09:11.862
Cuddles is really having to wrestle it through there.

212
00:09:12.589 --> 00:09:13.561
Up to Gambon.

213
00:09:13.597 --> 00:09:14.962
He's taking it very gingerly

214
00:09:15.082 --> 00:09:15.971
and I'm not surprised.

215
00:09:16.042 --> 00:09:16.710
Here we are.

216
00:09:16.780 --> 00:09:18.526
and across the line.

217
00:09:20.424 --> 00:09:21.713
Got the time here.

218
00:09:25.127 --> 00:09:26.521
The time is...

219
00:09:26.744 --> 00:09:29.908
1.29.6

220
00:09:30.630 --> 00:09:32.400
Top Gear top tip:

221
00:09:33.021 --> 00:09:35.845
if you want a slow car that looks like a Golf.

222
00:09:36.103 --> 00:09:37.122
get a Golf.

223
00:09:38.781 --> 00:09:42.198
That's interesting. the Stig didn't spin that car once in that lap...

224
00:09:42.304 --> 00:09:44.015
Anyway. it's time now for the news...

225
00:09:44.073 --> 00:09:46.382
You may notice we've got some new furniture.

226
00:09:46.722 --> 00:09:47.905
And a new telly...

227
00:09:48.651 --> 00:09:50.022
Now. the problem is. you see.

228
00:09:50.069 --> 00:09:52.201
There was a fire at our storage depot

229
00:09:52.272 --> 00:09:53.549
you might have seen it in the papers.

230
00:09:53.631 --> 00:09:55.424
And nearly all of our props got...

231
00:09:55.530 --> 00:09:56.303
destroyed.

232
00:09:56.385 --> 00:09:58.494
Yeah. and the police are saying.

233
00:09:58.604 --> 00:10:00.702
you can see it here. that it was arson.

234
00:10:00.784 --> 00:10:01.557
Yeah. but...

235
00:10:01.604 --> 00:10:02.811
I mean. who'd do that?

236
00:10:02.881 --> 00:10:04.253
It's not like we've ever upset anyone...

237
00:10:04.311 --> 00:10:04.979
I know!

238
00:10:06.655 --> 00:10:07.487
Well. there was the vicar

239
00:10:07.534 --> 00:10:09.796
whose tree I rammed in a Toyota pickup truck...

240
00:10:09.861 --> 00:10:11.056
and everyone in Wales...

241
00:10:11.607 --> 00:10:14.009
and everyone in Birmingham. everyone in America...

242
00:10:14.174 --> 00:10:14.701
Yeah.

243
00:10:14.830 --> 00:10:16.724
And while we were making this series. actually

244
00:10:16.771 --> 00:10:18.001
we managed to upset

245
00:10:18.095 --> 00:10:18.845
the Coast Guard.

246
00:10:18.915 --> 00:10:20.919
who said that we've ruined the English Channel.

247
00:10:21.224 --> 00:10:22.325
Hang on a minute!

248
00:10:22.431 --> 00:10:22.771
What?

249
00:10:22.853 --> 00:10:25.232
You're not seriously suggesting that the British Coast Guard

250
00:10:25.498 --> 00:10:27.970
drove all the way up to Watford and set fire to our...

251
00:10:28.029 --> 00:10:28.720
chairs.

252
00:10:28.908 --> 00:10:29.423
are you?

253
00:10:29.447 --> 00:10:30.490
No. I'm not!

254
00:10:30.548 --> 00:10:31.966
I know who did this...

255
00:10:32.540 --> 00:10:32.998
Who?

256
00:10:33.619 --> 00:10:34.474
Fifth Gear.

257
00:10:36.649 --> 00:10:37.645
Hang on. why?

258
00:10:38.091 --> 00:10:39.391
Can we just look at the evidence?

259
00:10:39.802 --> 00:10:41.677
Just last week ok? It was in the papers.

260
00:10:41.735 --> 00:10:42.802
They've rolled

261
00:10:42.884 --> 00:10:44.454
a Bedford Rascal van.

262
00:10:44.485 --> 00:10:45.400
There it is. ok?

263
00:10:45.540 --> 00:10:48.177
A year ago. if we look at a shot from Top Gear...

264
00:10:48.610 --> 00:10:50.989
WE rolled a Bedford Rascal van.

265
00:10:51.036 --> 00:10:53.802
They're now saying that one of their presenters has hurt his foot...

266
00:10:54.235 --> 00:10:56.040
That's not an accident!

267
00:10:57.363 --> 00:10:59.741
WE have proper accidents on this show!

268
00:11:00.441 --> 00:11:01.765
You think they're a bit... jelous?

269
00:11:04.065 --> 00:11:06.104
Tiff. Vicky. stop burning our things...

270
00:11:06.197 --> 00:11:06.561
Yes.

271
00:11:07.797 --> 00:11:09.789
Can I just say? The seats we used to have

272
00:11:09.918 --> 00:11:11.383
were from a Vauxhall Senator.

273
00:11:11.565 --> 00:11:13.768
So if anybody out there's watching and they have a Vauxhall Senator...

274
00:11:13.862 --> 00:11:15.960
Hang on. you're gonna say: "If you got a Vauxhall Senator

275
00:11:16.007 --> 00:11:17.354
and you don't need the seats..."

276
00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:20.073
Write to us at:

277
00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:22.874
<i>I've got a Vauxhall Senator and I drive everywhere standing up.

