00:33:13.056 --> 00:33:14.689
They're going to shout at me.

818
00:33:25.321 --> 00:33:26.954
Tell me we've stopped here

819
00:33:27.163 --> 00:33:28.628
to steal some wheels or something.

820
00:33:28.733 --> 00:33:29.863
It could be worse.

821
00:33:29.946 --> 00:33:33.274
How could this be worse...?! Is that the motorway?

822
00:33:34.148 --> 00:33:36.973
Oh. Jeremy. I always wanted to stay in the Italian lakes.

823
00:33:37.078 --> 00:33:38.480
We're staying here tonight.

824
00:33:38.731 --> 00:33:39.506
Well. yes.

825
00:33:39.673 --> 00:33:41.557
So we're carrying on by bicycle tomorrow?

826
00:33:41.787 --> 00:33:43.356
Because these will be stolen. obviously.

827
00:33:43.482 --> 00:33:46.056
They did say they had a secure car park

828
00:33:46.182 --> 00:33:47.856
that nobody could break into

829
00:33:47.961 --> 00:33:49.844
And I can see exactly what they mean:

830
00:33:49.970 --> 00:33:51.288
there's absolutely no way

831
00:33:51.393 --> 00:33:54.114
that anybody could possibly get into this car park

832
00:33:54.198 --> 00:33:56.143
in any way. shape or form.

833
00:33:56.289 --> 00:33:57.796
It's actually very simple.

834
00:33:57.963 --> 00:34:00.433
- What were you thinking?
- Do you know my car doesn't have a key

835
00:34:00.513 --> 00:34:01.476
or a lock?

836
00:34:01.622 --> 00:34:04.252
Did they save weight by not fitting locks to it?

837
00:34:04.440 --> 00:34:06.135
To be continued...

838
00:34:12.504 --> 00:34:13.383
I know.

839
00:34:13.613 --> 00:34:14.622
I'm sorry.

840
00:34:15.342 --> 00:34:16.196
Sorry.

841
00:34:16.949 --> 00:34:18.774
That hotel had

842
00:34:18.925 --> 00:34:19.946
no bar.

843
00:34:20.113 --> 00:34:21.185
no restaurant.

844
00:34:21.336 --> 00:34:22.608
no air conditioning in the rooms.

845
00:34:22.742 --> 00:34:24.404
No. it was like being in his car.

846
00:34:24.554 --> 00:34:25.693
Which is why

847
00:34:25.760 --> 00:34:27.149
we left the crew behind

848
00:34:27.283 --> 00:34:29.008
and us three all went

849
00:34:29.108 --> 00:34:29.996
nearer to the lakes

850
00:34:30.063 --> 00:34:31.151
to find another hotel.

851
00:34:31.302 --> 00:34:32.792
And the lakes are to the North.

852
00:34:32.876 --> 00:34:33.294
Yes.

853
00:34:33.378 --> 00:34:34.617
And which way did you take us?

854
00:34:34.701 --> 00:34:35.253
North.

855
00:34:35.370 --> 00:34:35.973
- East.
- East.

856
00:34:36.074 --> 00:34:38.546
- Yes...
- You made us drive 200km

857
00:34:38.613 --> 00:34:39.919
in the wrong direction.

858
00:34:40.002 --> 00:34:41.375
I did that. I did do that.

859
00:34:41.442 --> 00:34:43.820
But we found a hotel in the end. and all was well.

860
00:34:43.971 --> 00:34:45.561
You ruined our holiday!

861
00:34:45.628 --> 00:34:47.688
I did ruin your holiday. and I'm very sorry about that.

862
00:34:47.755 --> 00:34:50.601
We must now move on. because it's time to meet our guest.

863
00:34:50.701 --> 00:34:53.214
Now. the Star In A Reasonably Priced Car tonight

864
00:34:53.281 --> 00:34:54.637
once said that she and her husband

865
00:34:54.704 --> 00:34:58.036
set their alarm clock an hour early every morning so they had chance

866
00:34:58.136 --> 00:34:59.258
to make love

867
00:34:59.325 --> 00:35:00.664
before going to work.

868
00:35:00.832 --> 00:35:02.154
Much like James May.

869
00:35:02.255 --> 00:35:03.912
although of course he lives alone.

870
00:35:06.853 --> 00:35:09.716
Ladies and gentlemen. star of everything that matters:

871
00:35:09.817 --> 00:35:11.625
Dame Helen Mirren!

872
00:35:22.669 --> 00:35:23.875
I can rest now.

873
00:35:24.479 --> 00:35:25.428
Have a seat.

874
00:35:28.331 --> 00:35:30.440
I can't tell you how excited I am

875
00:35:30.534 --> 00:35:32.233
to have you here.

876
00:35:32.315 --> 00:35:33.956
No. I really. genuinely mean it.

877
00:35:34.225 --> 00:35:34.846

878
00:35:34.905 --> 00:35:36.381
talks to you about <i>The Queen</i>. obviously

879
00:35:36.557 --> 00:35:38.409
<i>Prime Suspect</i> as well...

880
00:35:38.643 --> 00:35:40.108
But you were in <i>The Long Good Friday</i>.

881
00:35:40.169 --> 00:35:40.872
Yes. I was.

882
00:35:40.931 --> 00:35:43.075
Now. this to me. I don't know if anybody would agree with this.

883
00:35:43.169 --> 00:35:44.601
is just the greatest film of all time...

884
00:35:44.657 --> 00:35:47.788
You know. three quarters have never heard of <i>The Long Good Friday</i>.

885
00:35:47.894 --> 00:35:50.062
- Have you heard...?  Yes?
- they're far too young.

886
00:35:50.155 --> 00:35:51.573
This audience you see.

887
00:35:51.661 --> 00:35:53.262
- Yeah?
- Well edu... well...

888
00:35:53.332 --> 00:35:54.551
well educated.

889
00:35:55.535 --> 00:35:56.367
They have heard of it.

890
00:35:56.426 --> 00:35:57.504
But you live in LA....

891
00:35:57.539 --> 00:35:58.852
... I've been trying to clear this up. now?

892
00:35:58.910 --> 00:36:00.856
No. I live in Woping. actually.

893
00:36:00.938 --> 00:36:01.531
You live in Woping?

894
00:36:01.590 --> 00:36:03.008
You've got a house in Los Angeles...

895
00:36:03.066 --> 00:36:05.433
My husband's American so we obviously spend a lot of time there.

896
00:36:05.515 --> 00:36:08.011
- Is it normal over there?
- In that car culture. you know.

897
00:36:09.242 --> 00:36:10.461
- Is it what. there?
- Normal.

898
00:36:10.601 --> 00:36:11.686
In Los Angeles.

899
00:36:11.733 --> 00:36:12.471
No. it's weird.

900
00:36:12.553 --> 00:36:13.374
It's LA.

901
00:36:13.456 --> 00:36:15.893
I'd have thought you'd love it 'cos people live in their cars

902
00:36:15.940 --> 00:36:18.354
and they do everything in their cars.

903
00:36:22.403 --> 00:36:23.470
Now. your autobiography.

904
00:36:23.599 --> 00:36:25.216
I've actually read it and liked it.

905
00:36:25.263 --> 00:36:26.048
No! Really?

906
00:36:26.095 --> 00:36:27.618
Yeah. I have. And what's more I got to one chapter

907
00:36:27.665 --> 00:36:29.083
where I went a bit white when you say

908
00:36:29.165 --> 00:36:30.419
- that when you were living in Parsons Green.

909
00:36:30.489 --> 00:36:31.110
Yes. I did...

910
00:36:31.160 --> 00:36:33.117
- and I think I know what you're going over...
- this is in Fulham in South West London.

911
00:36:33.867 --> 00:36:35.660
You. what is it? you became

912
00:36:35.718 --> 00:36:37.300
disillusioned with British society

913
00:36:37.379 --> 00:36:39.980
because of all the young hoorays living round there.

914
00:36:40.027 --> 00:36:42.148
- throwing bread rolls.
- Yes.

915
00:36:42.254 --> 00:36:43.367
I... That was me.

916
00:36:43.988 --> 00:36:45.441
I did live in Parsons Green.

917
00:36:45.488 --> 00:36:46.519
- You didn't?
- And I may...

918
00:36:46.578 --> 00:36:48.004
- I did...
- And did you throw food?

919
00:36:48.074 --> 00:36:48.496
Yes.

920
00:36:50.277 --> 00:36:52.703
I used to order it for its aerodynamic efficiency.

921
00:36:52.762 --> 00:36:55.820
You're one of those ghastly. ghastly guys...

922
00:36:55.879 --> 00:36:56.488
ohmygod!

923
00:36:56.558 --> 00:36:58.117
that drove me out of England.

924
00:37:00.069 --> 00:37:01.241
Didn't you also say

925
00:37:01.299 --> 00:37:03.221
somewhere just the other day that I was reading.

926
00:37:03.280 --> 00:37:05.014
that I remind you of Paris Hilton?

927
00:37:05.541 --> 00:37:08.518
Yes. I said you were like her. certainly. yes. I did.

928
00:37:08.643 --> 00:37:10.946
I wake up every morning and go. "Paris...?"

929
00:37:11.076 --> 00:37:12.855
- "Oh. no. I'm not."
- The thing is.

930
00:37:13.117 --> 00:37:14.844
Jeremy. you are uber-male.

931
00:37:15.001 --> 00:37:16.774
and Paris is uber-female.

932
00:37:16.983 --> 00:37:18.370
I think that you're both...

933
00:37:18.527 --> 00:37:20.829
you're the two sides of the same coin.

934
00:37:20.960 --> 00:37:23.157
I don't put pictures of myself naked on the Internet.

935
00:37:23.210 --> 00:37:25.747
That's one thing I don't do

936
00:37:25.878 --> 00:37:27.134
Maybe I'll give it a whirl.

937
00:37:27.265 --> 00:37:30.770
Neither did she. to her credit. if someone else did it.

938
00:37:30.979 --> 00:37:32.837
Here's a tip. Paris. if you're watching:

939
00:37:32.994 --> 00:37:34.250
Have sex without a camera.

940
00:37:36.604 --> 00:37:38.802
Now. anyway. let's move on to motoring if we may.

941
00:37:39.577 --> 00:37:41.539
I don't think we're gonna agree on much here. actually.

942
00:37:41.696 --> 00:37:43.946
Because you're not really a big car fan.

943
00:37:44.459 --> 00:37:46.588
No. my first car was a disaster.

944
00:37:46.816 --> 00:37:49.391
It was an MG Midget. Those little white things.

945
00:37:49.636 --> 00:37:51.952
My brother sold it to me.

946
00:37:52.156 --> 00:37:54.650
The engine blew up within two days.

947
00:37:55.508 --> 00:37:57.143
Didn't you have a Golf GTI?

948
00:37:57.634 --> 00:38:01.190
Yes. I did. I did. That came to a sticky end.

949
00:38:01.435 --> 00:38:03.929
- my poor old Golf GTI.
- Why? What happened to it?

950
00:38:04.133 --> 00:38:07.035
I was doing theatre in...

951
00:38:07.526 --> 00:38:11.205
at the Old... no. the Young Vic. excuse me. in Waterloo.

952
00:38:11.450 --> 00:38:14.066
and I'd just cleared out my closet and I had all this stuff

953
00:38:14.271 --> 00:38:16.315
to take to the charity shop.

954
00:38:16.519 --> 00:38:18.563
And then I thought. well... you know...

955
00:38:18.808 --> 00:38:20.688
there were no charity shops. I didn't have the time....

956
00:38:20.852 --> 00:38:23.795
and I knew everyone said: keep your car locked

957
00:38:23.999 --> 00:38:26.575
around here because things get nicked out of the car.

958
00:38:26.724 --> 00:38:27.827
So I thought. "Perfect.

959
00:38:27.991 --> 00:38:29.340
I'll leave my stuff in the car.

960
00:38:29.441 --> 00:38:30.927
I'll leave the car open

961
00:38:31.031 --> 00:38:32.036
and it'll all get nicked."

962
00:38:32.140 --> 00:38:33.731
Well. instead of the stuff getting nicked.

963
00:38:33.836 --> 00:38:35.259
my car got torched.

964
00:38:36.577 --> 00:38:37.435
- No!
- Yeah...

965
00:38:37.477 --> 00:38:40.010
I came out and it was like this hulk.

966
00:38:40.177 --> 00:38:41.349
So what have you got now?

967
00:38:41.475 --> 00:38:43.107
I don't have a car now.

968
00:38:44.070 --> 00:38:45.786
Have you got an Oyster Card. then?

969
00:38:46.142 --> 00:38:47.063
Yes. I do. yeah.

970
00:38:47.251 --> 00:38:48.109
What is one?

971
00:38:49.390 --> 00:38:50.582
It's a brilliant thing.

972
00:38:50.729 --> 00:38:51.796
It's this little thing

973
00:38:51.901 --> 00:38:53.973
and when you go on public transport...

974
00:38:54.224 --> 00:38:56.129
which are like buses

975
00:38:56.275 --> 00:38:58.598
and tubes and trains.

976
00:38:58.703 --> 00:38:59.896
you have this little card

977
00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:01.277
and you swipe it and pop!

978
00:39:01.326 --> 00:39:01.654
you're on.

979
00:39:01.760 --> 00:39:03.459
Why wouldn't you go in a car though?

980
00:39:03.553 --> 00:39:05.205
And there's a chauffeur driving the bus.

981
00:39:05.628 --> 00:39:07.035
you know. in a uniform.

982
00:39:07.128 --> 00:39:09.343
And the tramp sitting next to you. vomiting on you.

983
00:39:11.089 --> 00:39:12.882
Let's talk about supercars briefly.

984
00:39:13.105 --> 00:39:14.335
What's a supercar?

985
00:39:14.476 --> 00:39:16.364
Ferraris. Lamborghinis....

986
00:39:16.452 --> 00:39:18.057
where are you on those?

987
00:39:18.421 --> 00:39:19.358
What do you think of a...

988
00:39:19.405 --> 00:39:20.014
you know. a...

989
00:39:20.530 --> 00:39:22.217
a middle-aged chap in a Lambo?

990
00:39:23.881 --> 00:39:24.655
Well. I think I...

991
00:39:25.810 --> 00:39:27.392
I just think most guys who...

992
00:39:27.486 --> 00:39:28.048
drive them...

993
00:39:28.095 --> 00:39:29.677
When I see them I go.

994
00:39:29.794 --> 00:39:30.673
"Dickhead...".  you know.

995
00:39:37.329 --> 00:39:38.325
Oh... Sorry.

996
00:39:39.755 --> 00:39:41.466
Probably should have said "Pillock".

997
00:39:41.555 --> 00:39:42.914
Richard Hammond's got one.

998
00:39:44.063 --> 00:39:45.176
No. he hasn't. has he?

999
00:39:45.785 --> 00:39:46.477
He has.

1000
00:39:46.512 --> 00:39:47.238
He's not a...

1001
00:39:47.356 --> 00:39:48.176
He's not a pillock.

1002
00:39:48.223 --> 00:39:49.313
he's a nice guy.

1003
00:39:49.383 --> 00:39:50.051
So I'm sorry. Richard.

1004
00:39:50.109 --> 00:39:50.625
Is he?

1005
00:39:50.859 --> 00:39:52.125
- Yes.
- I thought he was a pillock.

1006
00:39:54.007 --> 00:39:54.909
So. OK.

1007
00:39:54.968 --> 00:39:56.022
the lap. obviously.

1008
00:39:56.093 --> 00:39:56.608
Was it fun?

1009
00:39:56.936 --> 00:40:00.639
I don't know if fun is the right word.
It was...

1010
00:40:00.733 --> 00:40:01.707
terrifying.

1011
00:40:01.824 --> 00:40:03.008
it was nerve-wracking.

1012
00:40:03.066 --> 00:40:05.351
it was adrenaline-pumping...

1013
00:40:05.480 --> 00:40:07.800
My hands were shaking like this at the end.

1014
00:40:07.929 --> 00:40:09.664
It was sweat-making.

1015
00:40:09.828 --> 00:40:10.765
It was...

1016
00:40:11.393 --> 00:40:12.488
It was fabulous.

1017
00:40:12.635 --> 00:40:13.854
- You did like it?
- It was fabulous.

1018
00:40:13.913 --> 00:40:15.471
Oh. that. I was thinking...

1019
00:40:18.389 --> 00:40:19.573
Shall we have a look at it?

1020
00:40:19.768 --> 00:40:20.858
Yeah.

1021
00:40:20.940 --> 00:40:22.475
Right. Sorry about the television.

1022
00:40:22.534 --> 00:40:24.784
but here we go. it's like being in the '60s.

1023
00:40:26.982 --> 00:40:28.446
That's an aggressive start.

1024
00:40:29.103 --> 00:40:30.380
Later. hard.

1025
00:40:30.954 --> 00:40:31.482
hold...

1026
00:40:32.032 --> 00:40:32.642
Later...

1027
00:40:33.239 --> 00:40:33.696
hard...

1028
00:40:34.290 --> 00:40:36.298
You doing the shipping forecasting. there?

1029
00:40:37.653 --> 00:40:38.590
Douglas.

1030
00:40:38.684 --> 00:40:39.692
Dogger.

1031
00:40:39.797 --> 00:40:40.618
Hurd.

1032
00:40:42.024 --> 00:40:42.727
Later...

1033
00:40:43.683 --> 00:40:44.421
Hard!

1034
00:40:44.539 --> 00:40:45.488
Faroe...

1035
00:40:45.523 --> 00:40:46.332
What is that?

1036
00:40:46.390 --> 00:40:48.499
- Is that what The Stig told you to do?
- He did.

1037
00:40:48.582 --> 00:40:49.648
Did he tell you to do that?

1038
00:40:49.695 --> 00:40:51.019
Slower. harder...

1039
00:40:51.893 --> 00:40:53.281
Slow into the corners...

1040
00:40:53.335 --> 00:40:54.471
and then fast out!

1041
00:40:54.577 --> 00:40:55.854
It's slow...

1042
00:40:56.534 --> 00:40:57.343
- now go!
- now go!

1043
00:40:57.507 --> 00:40:58.936
No! You. idiot!

1044
00:41:01.006 --> 00:41:03.115
My language was a lot bluer than that.

1045
00:41:03.186 --> 00:41:04.112
Oh. yes.

1046
00:41:04.721 --> 00:41:06.151
Here we go. now we're coming up to...

1047
00:41:06.268 --> 00:41:08.471
- the Follow...
- It's such a silly-looking little car.

1048
00:41:09.495 --> 00:41:10.386
Did you like it?

1049
00:41:10.526 --> 00:41:11.065
No.

1050
00:41:11.124 --> 00:41:12.144
No. It's awful. isn't it?

1051
00:41:13.163 --> 00:41:14.429
Oh. yes!

1052
00:41:16.433 --> 00:41:17.424
I liked that bit there.

1053
00:41:17.495 --> 00:41:18.819
I liked cutting the corner there.

1054
00:41:18.936 --> 00:41:20.471
Now we're really picking up speed.

1055
00:41:22.791 --> 00:41:24.268
That's the wrong gear.

1056
00:41:24.373 --> 00:41:25.885
Oh. Was it? Is that fourth?

1057
00:41:26.002 --> 00:41:28.393
That was third. it was going ddd-rrr.

1058
00:41:29.993 --> 00:41:31.657
This is really picking up speed now.

1059
00:41:31.822 --> 00:41:33.240
This is Michael Gambon's Corner.

1060
00:41:33.310 --> 00:41:34.786
Where we nearly lost him.

1061
00:41:34.910 --> 00:41:35.824
And round there.

1062
00:41:35.895 --> 00:41:38.812
And there we are. ladies and gentlemen. across the line.

1063
00:41:45.429 --> 00:41:46.167
So...

1064
00:41:51.206 --> 00:41:53.902
Miraculously undamaged in the fire.

1065
00:41:54.506 --> 00:41:55.467
is our board.

1066
00:41:55.854 --> 00:41:56.686
You had a fire?

1067
00:41:56.744 --> 00:41:59.357
Channel Five set fire to everything we own.

1068
00:41:59.915 --> 00:42:01.028
Honestly. they did.

1069
00:42:01.145 --> 00:42:02.516
That's why we're on rubbish furniture. I apologise...

1070
00:42:02.563 --> 00:42:04.508
But anyway. this survived

1071
00:42:04.567 --> 00:42:06.653
and where do you think you've come there?

1072
00:42:07.661 --> 00:42:09.336
If this is the thespian zone...

1073
00:42:09.418 --> 00:42:09.864
Yes.

1074
00:42:09.958 --> 00:42:11.735
Am I in the thespian zone?

1075
00:42:11.793 --> 00:42:12.297
Yes.

1076
00:42:13.656 --> 00:42:15.473
Ray Winstone. Kristin Scott Thomas...

1077
00:42:15.543 --> 00:42:15.895
Yes...

1078
00:42:16.117 --> 00:42:17.371
Rick Wakeman is not a thesp...

1079
00:42:17.442 --> 00:42:18.449
- He is actually.
- Yeah.

1080
00:42:18.672 --> 00:42:20.109
And then Brian Cox

1081
00:42:20.179 --> 00:42:22.218
- and Jimmy Carr. who's a comedian.
- I have no idea.

1082
00:42:22.300 --> 00:42:22.722
