when he gave the Swiss this place?

1353
00:54:03.451 --> 00:54:04.946
Plainly it should be ours.

1354
00:54:08.696 --> 00:54:10.674
This road was a test of brakes.

1355
00:54:10.791 --> 00:54:11.861
steering. grip.

1356
00:54:12.051 --> 00:54:13.237
power and handling.

1357
00:54:13.457 --> 00:54:14.761
An ideal place. then.

1358
00:54:14.893 --> 00:54:16.153
to reflect on the cars

1359
00:54:16.240 --> 00:54:18.300
we'd brought on our motoring holiday.

1360
00:54:24.833 --> 00:54:26.957
Everything about this car now has come alive.

1361
00:54:27.259 --> 00:54:29.119
It's suddenly in its element.

1362
00:54:37.258 --> 00:54:38.957
This thing just tracks

1363
00:54:39.104 --> 00:54:40.129
so perfectly.

1364
00:54:41.528 --> 00:54:42.510
Meanwhile.

1365
00:54:42.590 --> 00:54:44.260
in the Aston...

1366
00:54:44.883 --> 00:54:47.036
I wonder how much of this I have to endure

1367
00:54:47.168 --> 00:54:49.277
before I can admit that this is a terrible car

1368
00:54:49.351 --> 00:54:51.065
and that I hate it and I want to go home?

1369
00:54:55.512 --> 00:54:57.020
It's actually a physically

1370
00:54:57.138 --> 00:54:59.804
pleasurable sensation that runs up your arm

1371
00:54:59.994 --> 00:55:01.605
when you turn the wheel. It's....

1372
00:55:02.089 --> 00:55:03.524
... it's uncanny.

1373
00:55:06.832 --> 00:55:09.161
Jeremy Clarkson today married a Lamborghini

1374
00:55:09.293 --> 00:55:11.051
and moved to Switzerland.

1375
00:55:15.680 --> 00:55:17.013
And then it hit me...

1376
00:55:17.218 --> 00:55:18.375
I was in a Lamborghini.

1377
00:55:18.694 --> 00:55:19.720
in the Alps.

1378
00:55:20.789 --> 00:55:21.888
All I need

1379
00:55:22.005 --> 00:55:23.895
is a pair of sunglasses

1380
00:55:24.891 --> 00:55:26.614
and some Matt Monro.

1381
00:55:37.184 --> 00:55:38.063
Ooh. no.

1382
00:55:38.180 --> 00:55:39.338
hang on a minute.

1383
00:55:45.475 --> 00:55:46.120
We'd all

1384
00:55:46.231 --> 00:55:47.476
pretty much decided

1385
00:55:47.564 --> 00:55:49.102
that we'd found driving heaven...

1386
00:55:49.161 --> 00:55:50.801
well. two of us had.

1387
00:55:51.753 --> 00:55:52.310
But then.

1388
00:55:52.369 --> 00:55:54.815
after we popped over the border and back into Italy.

1389
00:55:54.903 --> 00:55:56.558
we found a cherry

1390
00:55:56.954 --> 00:55:58.330
for the top of our cake.

1391
00:56:05.414 --> 00:56:06.777
The Stelvio Pass.

1392
00:56:07.656 --> 00:56:08.974
15 miles

1393
00:56:09.047 --> 00:56:10.644
of asphalt spaghetti

1394
00:56:10.805 --> 00:56:12.161
draped on an Alp.

1395
00:56:14.491 --> 00:56:16.234
It was stunning.

1396
00:56:30.026 --> 00:56:30.700
Shall we do it?

1397
00:56:46.248 --> 00:56:47.420
Here we go.

1398
00:56:58.230 --> 00:56:59.416
The drops!

1399
00:56:59.943 --> 00:57:00.954
It's impossible.

1400
00:57:02.853 --> 00:57:05.328
If you went over the edge here you'd have time to phone the insurance!

1401
00:57:08.961 --> 00:57:10.323
There's no other way of saying it:

1402
00:57:10.411 --> 00:57:12.682
This is a magnificent piece of road building.

1403
00:57:22.454 --> 00:57:24.212
Not like PlayStation. this:

1404
00:57:24.285 --> 00:57:26.468
you can't just press the reset button when you get it wrong.

1405
00:57:26.951 --> 00:57:28.958
You just go through the Pearly Gates...

1406
00:57:29.172 --> 00:57:30.182
on fire!

1407
00:57:32.848 --> 00:57:33.716
I hate to admit this.

1408
00:57:33.774 --> 00:57:35.743
but this Aston is starting to make

1409
00:57:35.825 --> 00:57:37.524
a certain amount of good sense.

1410
00:57:38.551 --> 00:57:40.016
Even the brakes have stopped squeaking!

1411
00:57:40.648 --> 00:57:41.856
Climbing up now past

1412
00:57:41.938 --> 00:57:43.496
8.000 feet.

1413
00:57:44.129 --> 00:57:45.359
I think. at this altitude.

1414
00:57:46.180 --> 00:57:46.977
the Lambo

1415
00:57:47.082 --> 00:57:48.418
has all the advantage.

1416
00:57:48.643 --> 00:57:49.487
I'll solve that. though.

1417
00:57:49.593 --> 00:57:50.647
with some bravery.

1418
00:57:56.701 --> 00:57:57.732
This is hard work.

1419
00:57:57.791 --> 00:58:01.142
If I had no air conditioning. I'd look ridiculous now.

1420
00:58:07.700 --> 00:58:10.160
What an extraordinary road!

1421
00:58:12.211 --> 00:58:13.207
Thank you. Italy.

1422
00:58:13.653 --> 00:58:15.493
Thank you. thank you. thank you.

1423
00:58:19.538 --> 00:58:20.804
We finished our run.

1424
00:58:21.296 --> 00:58:23.944
And. as the cars ticked themselves cool.

1425
00:58:24.530 --> 00:58:26.159
we knew their work was done.

1426
00:58:26.968 --> 00:58:28.093
Our quest

1427
00:58:28.362 --> 00:58:29.417
was at an end.

1428
00:58:31.371 --> 00:58:32.836
Davos to Stelvio:

1429
00:58:33.328 --> 00:58:35.016
the greatest driving road

1430
00:58:35.637 --> 00:58:36.621
in the world.

1431
00:59:15.655 --> 00:59:16.932
So. there you are. If...

1432
00:59:17.389 --> 00:59:19.170
if you're thinking of going on holiday next year.

1433
00:59:19.217 --> 00:59:20.846
forget the Center Parcs. just go there!

1434
00:59:20.905 --> 00:59:21.678
Yes! Now.

1435
00:59:21.760 --> 00:59:22.557
the cars.

1436
00:59:22.651 --> 00:59:23.518
So...

1437
00:59:23.717 --> 00:59:24.385
James?

1438
00:59:25.146 --> 00:59:25.803
No!

1439
00:59:26.049 --> 00:59:27.959
Just no on every level.

1440
00:59:28.018 --> 00:59:28.498
Richard?

1441
00:59:28.627 --> 00:59:30.139
I thought the Porsche was fantastic. I loved it.

1442
00:59:30.256 --> 00:59:31.650
But the thing for me about that car.

1443
00:59:31.721 --> 00:59:33.627
the main problem is. I still don't see why

1444
00:59:34.001 --> 00:59:35.525
it's 15 grand more

1445
00:59:35.876 --> 00:59:37.904
for the RS version than the ordinary GT3.

1446
00:59:38.009 --> 00:59:39.392
I have to say the same on the Lambo:

1447
00:59:39.451 --> 00:59:41.326
I can't believe that I wouldn't have had as much fun

1448
00:59:41.419 --> 00:59:42.521
in a normal Gallardo.

1449
00:59:42.879 --> 00:59:43.700
the other thing is. well...

1450
00:59:44.110 --> 00:59:45.915
if you're going to do a special edition Lamborghini.

1451
00:59:45.973 --> 00:59:46.934
don't take stuff off.

1452
00:59:47.075 --> 00:59:47.790
put stuff on.

1453
00:59:47.860 --> 00:59:48.856
like space thrusters

1454
00:59:48.926 --> 00:59:50.872
and machine guns! That's what Lamborghinis

1455
00:59:51.012 --> 00:59:51.844
are about.

1456
00:59:51.961 --> 00:59:52.589
So. hang on.

1457
00:59:52.659 --> 00:59:53.831
we took three cars

1458
00:59:53.878 --> 00:59:54.792
on holiday

1459
00:59:55.179 --> 00:59:56.304
and they were all wrong.

1460
00:59:56.409 --> 00:59:58.062
Yes. we're back in business!

1461
00:59:58.167 --> 00:59:59.726
Yeah. Top Gear: ambitious.

1462
00:59:59.843 --> 01:00:01.191
- but rubbish!
- That's us.

1463
01:00:01.301 --> 01:00:02.614
And there'll be more of that next week!

1464
01:00:02.696 --> 01:00:03.926
See you then. good night!

1465
